trend_summary: Across the sequence the landscape stays predominantly agricultural with scattered villages. Built-up footprints enlarge only marginally around road junctions, while several fields are merged and hedgerows removed. Woodland blocks thicken, especially in the north-east, and a curving new distributor road appears south-central. Overall, change is modest and the area remains sparsely developed and rural.
notable_changes: Gradual expansion of woodland patches, particularly along the northern river corridor.
Consolidation of small fields into larger arable blocks; hedge removal visible in central belt.
Minor residential infill and edge-of-village growth around two southern settlements.
